<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-1641] auto-guessed memtable sizes are too high</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1641</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve seen two cases now of the memtable sizes being too large, causing OOMing.  Too-small memtables hurt performance, but too-large hurts worse when you start GC storming.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12477951">CASSANDRA-1641</key>
            <summary>auto-guessed memtable sizes are too high</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
